cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS

The paper deals with incorporating meta information into topic modeling, which is a common task in natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of Gibbs sampling algorithm and data augmentation techniques indicates that it could be categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also deals with improving the accuracy and quality of topic modeling, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
